{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://theme-fusion.com/?p=401479";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:623:"<p>Your website is much like an old-fashioned paper newsletter. It provides instant information on your church and its activities, all from the comfort of the reader&#8217;s home. And just like a paper newsletter, your website has to appeal to those viewing it. Your church may provide a great deal of value to your community, with activities and opinions [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://theme-fusion.com/creative-ways-engage-church-members-avada/">4 Creative Ways to Engage Church Members Using Avada</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://theme-fusion.com">Theme Fusion</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Tom Rankin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26050:"<p>Your website is much like an old-fashioned paper newsletter. It provides instant information on your church and its activities, all from the comfort of the reader&#8217;s home. And just like a paper newsletter, your website has to appeal to those viewing it. Your church may provide a great deal of value to your community, with activities and opinions of real interest to your congregation, but if your website can&#8217;t convince members to get involved, all that good work may go unnoticed.</p>\n<p><span id="more-401479"></span></p>\n<p>Avada is the answer! Along with its bundled plugins, Avada can provide the functionality you need to increase engagement and generate interest in your church without any coding or expert knowledge.</p>\n<p>With the above in mind, in this article we will explore four ways to enable members to engage with your church using Avada. We&#8217;ll be using <a href="http://avada.theme-fusion.com/church/" target="_blank">our Church demo</a> as an example. Let&#8217;s get started!</p>\n<h2>1. Create a Filterable and Searchable Events Calendar</h2>\n<p>Church events are an important part of community and togetherness that you don&#8217;t want your members to be missing. They&#8217;re also fantastic opportunities for others to get involved. By using the <a href="https://theme-fusion.com/avada-doc/special-features/how-to-use-the-events-calendar-with-avada/" target="_blank">Events Calendar plugin</a>, which is beautifully design integrated with Avada, we can offer a calendar that members can filter and search to conveniently find the event they’re looking for.</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-calendar-page-1-1024x763.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400651" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-calendar-page-1-1024x763.png" alt="The events page showcasing the calendar view." width="633" height="471" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-calendar-page-1-1024x763.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-calendar-page-1-300x223.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-calendar-page-1-768x572.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>You can add new events through your WP Admin Dashboard under <em>Events &gt; Add New</em>:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-tab-1.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400451" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-tab-1.png" alt="The Events Calendar tab" width="386" height="332" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-tab-1.png 772w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-tab-1-300x258.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-tab-1-768x661.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 386px) 100vw, 386px" /></a></figure>\n<p>We&#8217;ll skip an explanation of the top half of the <em>Event editor</em> page in this article (seeing as its layout is the same as creating a page or post) and focus our attention on <em>The Events Calendar</em> section at the bottom. What looks like a complex set of options really isn&#8217;t. Firstly, there&#8217;s a section to choose a date and time…</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-time-date-1024x186.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400602" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-time-date-1024x186.png" alt="Events Calendar options showing time and date selections." width="633" height="115" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-time-date-1024x186.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-time-date-300x55.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-time-date-768x140.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>…and underneath that are sections for adding a location (which enables you to show an embedded Google map) and event organizer:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-location-organizer-1024x258.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400601" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-location-organizer-1024x258.png" alt="The Events Calendar plugin options, showing location and organizer options." width="633" height="160" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-location-organizer-1024x258.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-location-organizer-300x76.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/events-calendar-location-organizer-768x194.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>Once you click <em>Publish</em>, that&#8217;s it! Your event is live and searchable by all the viewers of your church website:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-page-1024x745.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400600" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-page-1024x745.png" alt="An on-site event created with the Events Calendar plugin." width="633" height="460" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-page-1024x745.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-page-300x218.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/event-page-768x559.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>There are also additional options within the <em>Settings</em> dashboard tab which enable you to show comments on events pages, change the number of events shown per page and much more.</p>\n<h2>2. Build Anticipation With a Countdown Timer</h2>\n<p>If an upcoming event holds a special degree of importance; for example, an event centered around a holiday. You can use a countdown timer here:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/countdown-timer-1024x134.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400611" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/countdown-timer-1024x134.png" alt="The Countdown Timer shown on-site." width="633" height="83" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/countdown-timer-1024x134.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/countdown-timer-300x39.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/countdown-timer-768x100.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>To add a countdown timer to your page, click the <em>+ Element</em> button on a column in your Fusion Builder editor and select the <em>Countdown</em> element within the <em>Builder Elements</em> tab. </p>\n<p><em>To learn more about the Avada Fusion Builder, you can checkout our <a href="https://theme-fusion.com/support/video-tutorials/fusion-builder-videos/" target="_blank">video overview here.</a></p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/countdown-timer-element-blog-post1.jpg"><img src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/countdown-timer-element-blog-post1.jpg" alt="Countdown Timer Element" width="633" height="293" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-426001" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/countdown-timer-element-blog-post1.jpg 633w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/countdown-timer-element-blog-post1-300x139.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>This will open a modal window where the element&#8217;s settings can be configured. There are a number of options here to tinker with, but the main ones we need are <em>Countdown Timer End</em> (Where you add the event date.), <em>Heading Text</em> and <em>Subheading Text:</em></p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-end-date.png"><img src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-end-date.png" alt="countdown-end-date" width="1066" height="166" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-426250" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-end-date.png 1066w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-end-date-300x47.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-end-date-768x120.png 768w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-end-date-1024x159.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1066px) 100vw, 1066px" /></a></figure>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-timer-text.png"><img src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-timer-text.png" alt="countdown-timer-text" width="1066" height="243" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-426251" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-timer-text.png 1066w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-timer-text-300x68.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-timer-text-768x175.png 768w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-timer-text-1024x233.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1066px) 100vw, 1066px" /></a></figure>\n<p>There are further options for adding a link to the event in question, but you&#8217;re not limited to purely on-site events. For example, if you&#8217;re hosting an event on behalf of another community group with their own website, you may want to direct members there instead:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-element-link-settings.png"><img src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-element-link-settings.png" alt="countdown-element-link-settings" width="1059" height="235" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-426253" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-element-link-settings.png 1059w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-element-link-settings-300x67.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-element-link-settings-768x170.png 768w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/countdown-element-link-settings-1024x227.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1059px) 100vw, 1059px" /></a></figure>\n<p>Finally, the <em>Countdown</em> element has a myriad of style options, as well as <em>CSS Class</em> and <em>ID</em> sections to add custom CSS styling if desired.</p>\n<h2>3. Launch a Community Forum</h2>\n<p>Forums have been around almost as long as the internet itself; that&#8217;s because they&#8217;re invaluable for creating an online community. You and your members can use this to discuss recent events, sermons, or even personal topics relevant to your members. With the design integrated <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/bbpress/" target="_blank">bbPress plugin</a>, Avada enables you to launch a vibrant and active forum on your site.</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-screenshot-1024x626.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400636" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-screenshot-1024x626.png" alt="A forum page created with the bbPress plugin." width="633" height="387" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-screenshot-1024x626.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-screenshot-300x183.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-screenshot-768x469.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>The option to create a new forum can be found in your WP Admin sidebar under the <em>Forums</em> tab:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/new-forum-tab.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400614" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/new-forum-tab.png" alt="The dashboard tab for creating a new forum." width="325" height="107" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/new-forum-tab.png 650w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/new-forum-tab-300x99.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 325px) 100vw, 325px" /></a></figure>\n<p>Once you&#8217;re in the <em>Create New Forum</em> screen, give your forum a title and look to the <em>Forum Attributes</em> box:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-attributes.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400613" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-attributes.png" alt="The Forum Attributes meta box" width="302" height="319" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-attributes.png 604w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/forum-attributes-284x300.png 284w" sizes="(max-width: 302px) 100vw, 302px" /></a></figure>\n<p>Here you can choose whether to create a forum or a category, set its status as <em>Open</em> or <em>Closed</em> and determine its visibility choosing from <em>Public</em>, <em>Private</em>, or <em>Hidden</em>. For creating sub-forums, you can also specify which parent forum it belongs to.</p>\n<p>Finally, the <em>Topics</em> and <em>Replies</em> tabs within the dashboard enables you to carry out basic moderation of member activity. Topics can be set to &#8216;sticky&#8217; from here. Also, topics along with replies can be edited, trashed, or marked as spam:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/topics-screen-1024x224.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400615" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/topics-screen-1024x224.png" alt="An entry on the Topics screen." width="633" height="138" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/topics-screen-1024x224.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/topics-screen-300x66.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/topics-screen-768x168.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<h2>4. Publish Video and Audio Sermons</h2>\n<p>With the convenience of the internet, members unable to attend church no longer have to worry about the sermons they&#8217;ve missed. Those who did attend can listen again or share their favorite sermons when you archive them on your church website:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sermon-video-page-1024x313.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400617" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sermon-video-page-1024x313.png" alt="A sermon displayed on the Sermons page." width="633" height="193" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sermon-video-page-1024x313.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sermon-video-page-300x92.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/sermon-video-page-768x235.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>First of all, it&#8217;s worth pointing out that you&#8217;ll need to upload your sermons to your favorite video site. That&#8217;s likely either <a href="https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/57407" target="_blank">YouTube</a> or <a href="https://vimeo.com/upload" target="_blank">Vimeo</a>. Once that&#8217;s done, Avada&#8217;s Fusion Builder provides elements to embed both YouTube and Vimeo content on your site. There is also a <a href="https://soundcloud.com/" target="_blank">SoundCloud</a> element for embedding audio sermons. And just like the Countdown Timer, adding the media embed elements is very simple. Just click the <em>&#8220;+ Element&#8221;</em> button in the column you want your embed to be in and a modal window with available elements will open:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/adding-media-elements.jpg"><img src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/adding-media-elements.jpg" alt="The Fusion Builder highlighting the different embedding options." width="633" height="477" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-426023" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/adding-media-elements.jpg 633w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/adding-media-elements-300x226.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>Clicking your desired element will open the options screen for that element. The important option we need is the <em>Video ID</em> or <em>Soundcloud URL</em> depending on your media source. If you&#8217;re using Vimeo, it will look like the below example. You can get the video ID by navigating to that video on the site:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-browser1-1024x212.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400620" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-browser1-1024x212.png" alt="The URL bar highlighting the video ID needed to embed content with Avada." width="633" height="131" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-browser1-1024x212.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-browser1-300x62.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-browser1-768x159.png 768w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-browser1.png 1064w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>…then copy and paste the string of numbers at the end of the URL into the <em>Video ID</em> box:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-option-1024x107.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400619" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-option-1024x107.png" alt="The Vimeo embedding element\'s Video ID text box" width="633" height="66" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-option-1024x107.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-option-300x31.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/video-id-option-768x80.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>It&#8217;s that simple! Now, let&#8217;s take things even further by creating a gallery showcasing your most recent sermons:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/recent-works-1024x457.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400621" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/recent-works-1024x457.png" alt="The Sermons page showing the Recent Sermons gallery." width="633" height="283" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/recent-works-1024x457.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/recent-works-300x134.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/recent-works-768x343.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>This is a little more complex, but by the end you&#8217;ll be able to create what you see above. For this, we&#8217;ll need to navigate to the <em>Portfolio</em> tab on the dashboard and click <em>Add New</em>:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portfolio-tab.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400625" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portfolio-tab.png" alt="The Portfolio dashboard tab." width="326" height="157" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portfolio-tab.png 652w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/portfolio-tab-300x144.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 326px) 100vw, 326px" /></a></figure>\n<p>This will take you to what looks like a normal WordPress post editor. You can title the sermon and add a description of the message to the post content area. That takes place in the top area of the post editor. Now, scroll down to Fusion Page Options. In these options under the <em>Portfolio</em> tab, you&#8217;ll find the <em>Video Embed Code</em> textarea:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-fusion-options-embed-code.jpg"><img src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-fusion-options-embed-code.jpg" alt="The Fusion Page Options Embed Code Field" width="633" height="781" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-426029" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-fusion-options-embed-code.jpg 633w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-fusion-options-embed-code-243x300.jpg 243w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>You&#8217;ll need something to put in here so Avada knows which video you want to embed. For that, we head to the video on our chosen hosting site as we did before. This time we click on the paper airplane icon to the right of the video:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/vimeo-share-icon-1024x396.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400629" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/vimeo-share-icon-1024x396.png" alt="A Vimeo video, with a highlighted Share icon." width="633" height="245" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/vimeo-share-icon-1024x396.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/vimeo-share-icon-300x116.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/vimeo-share-icon-768x297.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>A pop-up box will appear with the code you need. You can click on the text in the <em>Embed</em> section and it will expand and auto select the code you need. Right-click on the selection and copy the text. It will look something like the below image:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/share-box-embed-code-1024x869.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400627" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/share-box-embed-code-1024x869.png" alt="The Vimeo Share box, with highlighted Embed code." width="544" height="461" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/share-box-embed-code-1024x869.png 1024w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/share-box-embed-code-300x254.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/share-box-embed-code-768x652.png 768w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/share-box-embed-code.png 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 544px) 100vw, 544px" /></a></figure>\n<p>Head back to the <em>Video Embed Code</em> textarea in the <em>Fusion Page Options</em>. Now paste your code here. <strong>Special Note</strong>: There will be some additional HTML that you don&#8217;t need in this field. You can safely delete anything from <em>&lt;p&gt; </em>onwards:</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/delete-embed-code.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-400624" src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/delete-embed-code.png" alt="The Video Code Embed screen, with highlighted, text to delete." width="474" height="214" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/delete-embed-code.png 948w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/delete-embed-code-300x135.png 300w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/delete-embed-code-768x347.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a></figure>\n<p>Click <em>Update </em>at the top of the post editor and continue to add new entries in the <em>Portfolio</em> tab. Now we need to display them on your page. To do this, head to the <em>Pages</em> dashboard tab and find the page you&#8217;d like to display your sermons on. You&#8217;ll need to add the <em>Portfolio Element</em> to the page using the same method as the above element additions.</p>\n<figure><a href="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-element.jpg"><img src="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-element.jpg" alt="Portfolio Element in the builder." width="633" height="310" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-426036" srcset="https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-element.jpg 633w, https://theme-fusion.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/portfolio-element-300x147.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 633px) 100vw, 633px" /></a></figure>\n<p>As with previous elements, clicking on them in the element list will open their settings in a window. Configure as needed and click <em>&#8220;Save&#8221;</em> to add the element to the page. There are various layout options which you can experiment with to find a layout you like.</p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>A website that doesn&#8217;t engage with its visitors can mean that the important events and community activities you have planned go unnoticed by your congregation. Here are the steps you can take to get creative and engage your church members with Avada:</p>\n<div class="shortcode-list">\n<ol>\n<li>Use the Events Calendar plugin to create a searchable and filterable list of events.</li>\n<li>Add a Countdown Timer to build anticipation for your next event.</li>\n<li>Offer your members a chance to discuss church matters through a forum.</li>\n<li>Add video and audio of your sermons through a number of Fusion Builder elements.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n<p>Member engagement isn&#8217;t difficult. By following the above steps, you&#8217;re giving your members the best chance at getting involved with your church&#8217;s activities and staying informed (God willing!).</p>\n<p>How are you using Avada and Fusion Builder to engage your church members? Let us know in the comments section below!</p>\n<p><em>Image credit: <a href="https://pixabay.com/en/cross-community-church-christianity-1261976/" target="_blank">Buecherwurm_65</a>.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://theme-fusion.com/creative-ways-engage-church-members-avada/">4 Creative Ways to Engage Church Members Using Avada</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://theme-fusion.com">Theme Fusion</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"http://theme-fusion.com/creative-ways-engage-church-members-avada/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"6";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lan